Introduction

Go Youn-ha, better known by the mononym Younha, is a South Korean singer-songwriter and record producer.

She began her career in 2004 in Japan, where she was nicknamed the "Oricon Comet" for her success on the Japanese music chart. In 2006, she debuted in South Korea, where she is regarded as one of the country's best singer-songwriters.

She originally debuted in Japan with the single "Yubikiri -Japanese version-" on October 20, 2004 before officially debuting in Korea on December 17, 2006 with her debut stage on SBS's Inkigayo for the single "Audition".
